# Cline Rules — Solar Navigator

## Project Identity
Solar Navigator is an **AI agent coding experiment**: every feature is co-created with AI
coding agents; the human author directs and reviews only. Produce clean, idiomatic Rust
that future agents can extend with minimal context.

## Stack
- Rust 2024 · Bevy 0.18.1 ECS · bevy_egui · wgpu v27
- Optional `spice` Cargo feature → `rust-spice` → NAIF CSPICE C library
- `reqwest` for NASA JPL Horizons HTTP API
- WGSL custom atmosphere shader at `assets/shaders/planet_atmosphere.wgsl`

## Module Map
| File | Responsibility |
|------|---------------|
| `src/main.rs` | Entry point — calls `app::run()` |
| `src/ephemeris.rs` | `SpiceEphemeris` + Horizons HTTP client (no Bevy) |
| `src/app/mod.rs` | `App` construction, plugin registration, system scheduling |
| `src/app/types.rs` | All `Resource`s, `Component`s, and `BODIES` constant array |
| `src/app/setup.rs` | Startup: spawn scene, load textures, start Horizons sync task |
| `src/app/simulation.rs` | Update: keyboard input, time advance, body transforms |
| `src/app/camera.rs` | Update: orbit camera, fly-to animation, body tracking |
| `src/app/render.rs` | Update: lighting rig, visibility toggles, window title |
| `src/app/materials.rs` | `PlanetAtmosphereMaterial` (Bevy `ExtendedMaterial` + WGSL) |
| `src/app/ui.rs` | `egui` side panel (target search, sim speed, body list) |
| `src/app/util.rs` | Asset resolution, cubemap conversion, `format_simulation_speed` |

## Hard Rules
1. `pub(super)` for everything inside `app/` — no leakage.
2. Resources defined in `types.rs`; systems defined in their owning module.
3. Both feature variants must pass at all times:
   ```bash
   cargo check --all-targets
   cargo check --all-targets --no-default-features
   cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings
   cargo clippy --all-targets --no-default-features -- -D warnings
   cargo test --all-targets --no-default-features
   ```
4. No `unwrap()` / `expect()` in non-test production code.
5. Every `#[allow(clippy::...)]` must have a comment explaining why it is safe.

## Coordinate Remap (SPICE → Bevy)
```
scene.x =  spice.x * AU_TO_SCENE_UNITS   // X unchanged
scene.y =  spice.z * AU_TO_SCENE_UNITS   // ecliptic north → Bevy Y
scene.z = -spice.y * AU_TO_SCENE_UNITS   // negated, right-handed
```
`AU_TO_SCENE_UNITS = 250.0` — a fixed constant, not runtime-configurable.

## Adding a New Body
1. Add `BodySpec` entry to `BODIES` in `types.rs`.
2. Add `horizons_command_for_target` mapping in `ephemeris.rs`.
3. If SPICE kernels cover it, add it to `spice_supports_target` in `ephemeris.rs`.
